Afriforum accuses Julius Malema of being in contempt of court for singing shoot the Boer song. While the lobby group says Mbuyiseni Ndlozi incited violence by singing burn the Boers. The lobby group alleges that several farms were targeted just days later. Courtesy of #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - EFF leader Julius Malema says AfriForum's civil case against him is a waste of the court's time. Malema says the lobby group claims that the singing of 'Shoot the Boer incites violence is a distortion of its meaning. LIVESTREAM: AfriForum case over 'Shoot the Boer' song The EFF leader took the stand at the Equality Court in his own defence on Wednesday. Malema has been accused of hate speech for allegedly singing the song outside a court appearance in Senekal two years ago. READ: Malema: AfriForum's Roets not an expert on the EFF But the EFF leader has denied this. AfriForum insists the song vilifies white farmers and incites violence. Malema, however, insists farm murders can't be linked to the song as it dates back to the 70s.